[[File:Snipers conduct live-fire exercise during Exercise Eager Lion 150507-M-QZ288-047.jpg|thumb|right|[[Jordanian Armed Forces]] sniper.]]
[[File:140605-M-ET113-110.jpg|alt=|thumb|Marines with Battalion Landing Team 1/6, Charlie Company, 2nd Platoon]]
'''Eager Lion''' is a two-week multinational [[military exercise]] held annually in [[Jordan]] since 2010. It is organized by the [[U.S. Department of Defense]]<ref>http://www.upi.com/Top_News/World-News/2015/05/19/United-States-joins-17-nations-for-war-games-in-Jordan/8061432058426/</ref> 18 countries participated in the exercise in 2015 including, Jordan, the [[United Kingdom]], [[France]], [[Italy]], [[Pakistan]], the [[United States]], [[Canada]], [[Belgium]], [[Poland]], [[Australia]], [[Kuwait]], [[Bahrain]], [[Qatar]], [[Saudi Arabia]], [[Egypt]], the [[UAE]], [[Lebanon]], and [[Iraq]].<ref>http://www.jordantimes.com/news/local/eager-lion-2015-concludes-joint-drill</ref> The exercise revolves around troop deployments, chemical warfare, border security, command and control, cyber defense and battlespace management.<ref>http://www.defense.gov/News-Article-View/Article/759235/us-jordan-partner-in-eager-lion-exercise</ref>

The exercise "amounts to an outgrowth of the annual bilateral 'Infinite Moonlight' US-Jordan exercise that stretches back to the 1990s."<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.csmonitor.com/World/Middle-East/2012/0529/US-18-other-nations-wrap-up-Eager-Lion-military-exercise-in-Jordan|title=US, 18 other nations, wrap up Eager Lion military exercise in Jordan|date=2012-05-29|work=Christian Science Monitor|access-date=2017-12-10|issn=0882-7729}}</ref>

Eager Lion is now largest U.S. military exercise in the Middle East, having surpassed [[Operation Bright Star|Bright Star]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://williamaarkin.wordpress.com/2012/05/18/eager-lion-now-supplant-bright-star-as-largest-u-s-exercise-in-middle-east/|website=William M. Arkin Online|title=Eager Lion Now Supplants Bright Star as Largest U.S. Exercise in Middle East|date=May 18, 2012|first=William|last=Arkin|authorlink = William Arkin}}</ref> 

