{{Infobox building | name = Government House | native_name = Casa Guvernului din Chișinău | image = File:Casa Guvernului.jpg | location = [[Great National Assembly Square, Chișinău|Great National Assembly Square]]<ref name="rutraveller">{{cite web|url=https://www.rutraveller.ru/place/28242|website=rutraveller.ru|title=Здание правительства Молдовы: описание, фото, контакты, гиды, экскурсии|accessdate=2018-10-04}}</ref> | location_town = [[Chisinau]] | location_country = [[Moldova]] | coordinates = | start_date = | completion_date = 1964 | architect = [[Semyon Fridlin]] | owner = [[Government of Moldova]] | website = | current_tenants = [[Pavel Filip]] as [[Prime Minister of Moldova]] }}
The '''Government House in Chisinau''' ([[Moldovan language|Moldovan]]: Casa Guvernului din Chișinău) is a government building in [[Chisinau]] located on [[Great National Assembly Square, Chișinău|Great National Assembly Square]] and Stefan cel Mare Avenue. It was designed by [[Semyon Fridlin]] in 1964 on Victory Square (now PMAN) and along Lenin Avenue (now Stefan cel Mare Avenue). It used to be the headquarters of the Council of Ministers of the [[Moldovan SSR]]. The building is a 6-storey reinforced concrete structure, lined with white stone, made in the shape of a letter Russian letter ''П'' (translated to ''P'' in English). Above the main entrance to the building is the inscription "The Government of the Republic of Moldova", as well as the [[Coat of Arms of Moldova]] and the [[Flag of Moldova]].<ref name="informator">{{cite web|url=http://www.informator.md/ro/destinatii-turistice/moldova/chisinau/info_chisinau--casa_guvernului_din_chisinau-37-chisinau/prezentare-generala/|website=informator.md|title=Casa Guvernului din Chisinau Chişinău, descriere Casa Guvernului din Chisinau, Website, adresa electronica, localizare pe harta Casa Guvernului din Chisinau.|accessdate=2018-10-04}}</ref><ref name="mold">{{cite web|url=http://mold.su/kishinev/pravitelstvo-moldova|website=mold.su|title=Здание правительства Молдовы|accessdate=2018-10-04}}</ref> In 2010, the [[Monument to the Victims of the Soviet Occupation]] was opened right in front of the building.<ref name="publika">{{cite web|url=https://www.publika.md/primaria-a-instalat-in-fata-guvernului-o-piatra-in-memoria-victimelor-regimului-comunist_46911.html|author=PUBLIKA.MD - AICI SUNT ȘTIRILE|title=Primăria a instalat în faţa Guvernului o piatră în memoria victimelor regimului comunist &#124; PUBLIKA .MD - AICI SUNT ȘTIRILE|website=publika.md|accessdate=2018-10-04}}</ref>
