[[Monastir, Tunisia|Mounastir]] Radio is a public local radio created on August 1977. It broadcasts from [[Monastir, Tunisia|Mounastir]] city targeting locals of [[Center East Tunisia]]. == Content == The radio broadcasts 19.5 hours a day with content targeting mainly the audiences of [[Center East Tunisia]] with diverse programming. == Broadcast == Mounastir Radio broadcasts on FM in [[Center East Tunisia]]. The [[Frequency|frequencies]] vary from region to region. Sometimes the service is available in different [[Frequency|frequencies]]. In Mounastir, it is on 106.1&nbsp;MHz and in Sousse on 99&nbsp;MHz . It also broadcasts on 603 Kz MW . The internet service is not yet available, but there are some recorded programs on the Tunisian Radio website.
==See also== *[http://www.radiotunis.com Tunisia Radio Website]
